13:54.137 --> 13:58.402
Hey... Come play with me.

14:02.667 --> 14:04.191
[Vincent VO] Ditta...

14:09.718 --> 14:10.980
Ditta.

14:14.505 --> 14:16.377
Hey, Frankie!

14:16.420 --> 14:17.726
Come check this out.

14:18.292 --> 14:19.989
[choking]

14:22.949 --> 14:24.037
[mallet smashing]

14:29.999 --> 14:32.784
[Vincent] Come, my precious.

14:34.047 --> 14:36.266
I'm here for you.

14:36.310 --> 14:37.877
[growling]

14:50.933 --> 14:53.283
[crickets chirping]

14:55.938 --> 14:58.332
- [knocking at door]
- [breathing deeply]

15:02.640 --> 15:04.599
[groaning softly]

15:10.257 --> 15:12.085
[coughing]

15:13.521 --> 15:15.697
Hi, lollipop. I'm Janet.

15:15.740 --> 15:17.568
Oh, hair and makeup
at your service.

15:17.612 --> 15:20.484
[chuckles]
I love old houses.

15:20.528 --> 15:22.486
I grew up in a Victorian
just like this one.

15:22.530 --> 15:25.663
I so love the South Shore.
[giggles]

15:25.707 --> 15:28.144
Is... is this
the Miller residence?

15:28.188 --> 15:32.105
Yes, and... Oh, you must be
Christina Weingarten.

15:32.148 --> 15:35.325
I'm Mrs. O'Brian
and I work for Mr. Miller.

15:35.369 --> 15:38.372
Oh, yes, I wasn't sure
if this was the right address.

15:38.415 --> 15:39.721
One and the same.

15:39.764 --> 15:41.157
- Oh.
- Won't you come in?

15:41.201 --> 15:43.420
You can put
all of your stuff over there.

15:43.464 --> 15:46.989
Uh, Mr. Miller is dealing with
other family members

15:47.033 --> 15:49.731
so he asked me to situate you.

15:49.774 --> 15:51.994
Okay, well,
that was Janet Higgins.

15:52.038 --> 15:55.955
She's with makeup.
And this is my sister, Nancy.

15:55.998 --> 15:57.957
She's basically my...

15:58.000 --> 16:00.176
She's my everything department.

16:00.220 --> 16:02.744
My sister basically meansI do everything.

16:02.787 --> 16:04.876
- Well, Nancy,
very nice to meet you.
- Yeah.

16:04.920 --> 16:06.226
Come on in.

16:07.227 --> 16:11.361
And, um, this is Steve Cooper,

16:11.405 --> 16:13.537
and he goes by Scratch.

16:13.581 --> 16:16.018
- He does sounds.
- Hey, nice to meet you.

16:17.802 --> 16:20.718
- Hi, Seth, Seth Cosmo.
- Hi.

16:20.762 --> 16:22.372
How are you?

16:22.416 --> 16:24.026
Oh, my God.

16:24.070 --> 16:25.985
I've been calling you Sam
this whole time.

16:26.028 --> 16:28.161
No wonder why
you haven't been responding.

16:28.204 --> 16:30.424
Most people just call me Cosmo.I'm sorry, what's your name?

16:30.467 --> 16:32.121
Oh, Edna O'Brian.

16:32.165 --> 16:33.731
Ms. O'Brian, nice to meet you.

16:33.775 --> 16:36.734
This strapping gentlemanbehind me, Ottis Beaumont.

16:36.778 --> 16:37.909
He's my assistant.

16:37.953 --> 16:41.435
Ma'am. Where's the shitter?

16:41.478 --> 16:44.307
Coming up from Lake Kay,it was a mess.

16:44.351 --> 16:46.788
Traffic damn nearmade me shit myself.

16:46.831 --> 16:49.704
Never eat more than six slidersfrom The Castle.

16:49.747 --> 16:52.837
With coffee, you arejust asking for bodily harm.

16:52.881 --> 16:54.187
- It's-it's down the hall.
- Thank you.

16:54.230 --> 16:55.405
Right before the kitchen.

16:55.449 --> 16:58.234
It is downright inhumane.

16:58.278 --> 17:00.019
I just met him.

17:00.062 --> 17:01.324
He's got a colorful vocabulary.

17:01.368 --> 17:02.630
[laughs] I'll say.

17:02.673 --> 17:04.284
He was a referral.

17:04.327 --> 17:06.068
- Yeah.
- What are you gonna do?

17:06.112 --> 17:07.417
He's fine.

17:07.461 --> 17:09.289
Uh, you came with
a photographer, right?

17:09.332 --> 17:11.508
Yes, Lexy Collins.She's on her way.

17:11.552 --> 17:13.597
She's great,I work with her all the time.

17:13.641 --> 17:16.513
Oh, no, no, no.
Please, please, no smoking.

17:16.557 --> 17:19.734
Um, uh,
because of the oxygen here.

17:19.777 --> 17:21.779
Not a problem.I-I actually quit,

17:21.823 --> 17:24.565
I just kinda keep one with me,suppress the urge a little bit,

17:24.608 --> 17:26.958
you know what I mean?Actually did the same thingwhen I quit drinking.

17:27.002 --> 17:28.351
I've been sober for 14 years.

17:28.395 --> 17:31.050
[chuckles] Well,
I'm glad you found your peace.

17:31.093 --> 17:32.529
I'll put this away.

17:32.573 --> 17:35.402
Have you guys all worked
together for a long time?

17:35.445 --> 17:36.968
Um, no.

17:37.012 --> 17:39.884
I actually haven't
worked with Cosmo before,

17:39.928 --> 17:43.975
but I found him on the net,
and he seems like
he'll work out just fine.

17:44.019 --> 17:46.543
But Scratch and I haveworked together plenty of times.

17:46.587 --> 17:48.850
- Oh, is that everyone?
- Yup.

17:48.893 --> 17:51.809
And, oh, we parked
down the street
just like you said.

17:51.853 --> 17:56.945
And it seems like
I saw that you had parking.

17:56.988 --> 18:00.862
Oh-oh-oh, that's Mr. Miller's
funeral parlor.

18:00.905 --> 18:02.907
Oh, well....

18:02.951 --> 18:06.041
[chuckles] This is great.

18:06.085 --> 18:08.043
It's gonna be good.

18:08.087 --> 18:10.785
[train horn honking]

18:13.918 --> 18:18.184
[man over PA] The Manhattan bound will depart in five minutes.

18:18.227 --> 18:22.492
Repeat, Manhattan bound
will depart

18:22.536 --> 18:26.279
in five minutes in lane 14.

18:30.935 --> 18:34.156
Make yourselves comfortable.
Are you hungry?

18:34.200 --> 18:35.940
- Oh, yeah.
- I'm starving.

18:35.984 --> 18:37.246
[Mrs. O'Brian]
Well, good,

18:37.290 --> 18:39.379
'cause dinner
will be served shortly.

18:39.422 --> 18:44.079
And Mr. Miller
will be here to greet you.

18:44.123 --> 18:46.560
[knocking at door]

18:51.652 --> 18:53.175
[door opens]

18:53.219 --> 18:54.524
[Lexy] Hi.

18:54.568 --> 18:55.351
[Mrs. O'Brian] You must be--

18:55.395 --> 18:56.744
Lexy, Lexy Collins.

18:56.787 --> 18:59.225
- Please, come on in.
- Oh, thank you.

18:59.268 --> 19:00.835
Oh, God.

19:01.401 --> 19:02.793
Oh.

19:02.837 --> 19:04.534
[Mrs. O'Brian]
Um, put your stuff over there.

19:04.578 --> 19:07.755
- Oh, sure.
- And, um, go join the others.

19:08.669 --> 19:12.020
Oh, I didn't know you were here.

19:12.063 --> 19:15.415
Please,
come and meet your guests.

19:15.458 --> 19:19.680
Christina Weingarten and group,

19:19.723 --> 19:24.380
say hello to your host,
Vincent Miller.

19:26.861 --> 19:30.473
Oh, dear,
you didn't drink your tea?

19:30.517 --> 19:33.128
Oh, um, I did. I...

19:33.172 --> 19:36.175
[soft piano music]

19:36.218 --> 19:38.002
Delicious.

19:38.046 --> 19:39.352
[chuckles]

19:41.789 --> 19:45.096
Mrs. O'Brian,you've done enough this evening.

19:45.140 --> 19:48.187
Please, you can call it a night.

19:48.230 --> 19:51.320
Oh, um,I'll-I'll just finish up here--

19:51.364 --> 19:53.757
Leave it! I insist.

19:53.801 --> 19:54.976
Thank you.

19:55.019 --> 19:56.412
Um...

19:57.457 --> 19:59.241
Everybody have
a good night then.

19:59.285 --> 20:00.590
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- Goodnight.

20:00.634 --> 20:02.244
- Have a good night.
- Thank you.

20:02.288 --> 20:03.854
- Dinner was great, thank you.
- Dinner was so good.

20:03.898 --> 20:05.726
Delicious.

20:05.769 --> 20:08.729
Man, don't nobodycook no catfish no more.

20:09.164 --> 20:10.034
Catfish?

20:10.078 --> 20:12.211
It is an acquired taste.

20:12.254 --> 20:14.865
Not everyone appreciates it.

20:14.909 --> 20:17.955
Well, you sound like you knowsome good old Southern cooking,Mr. Miller.

20:17.999 --> 20:20.349
- Can you pass the dressing?
- Don't listen to them.

20:20.393 --> 20:21.959
Thank you.

20:25.006 --> 20:28.879
So... you get freaked outliving next to a funeral parlor?

20:28.923 --> 20:31.230
- I own it.
- [Christina clears throat]

20:31.273 --> 20:32.970
What made you land here?

20:33.014 --> 20:37.845
The 18th Amendment,what we now know as Prohibition.

20:39.499 --> 20:41.240
[scoffs] Come again?

20:41.283 --> 20:44.721
The lodge used to be
an orphanage.

20:44.765 --> 20:49.291
And during Prohibition,
it became a smuggler's dream.

20:49.335 --> 20:52.381
There's 118 miles
between New York Harbor

20:52.425 --> 20:54.078
and the tip of Montauk Point.

20:54.122 --> 20:56.864
The lodge was a rendezvous pointfor foreign liquor ships

20:56.907 --> 20:59.388
supplying the nation's
liquor markets.

20:59.432 --> 21:05.655
Until 1932 when a fire broke outand killed everybody.

21:07.266 --> 21:12.575
Okay. So, I'm stilla little lost on the here part.

21:12.619 --> 21:15.143
My family buried
most of the dead that year.

21:16.449 --> 21:21.062
And we converted the lodge
into a funeral home.

21:21.105 --> 21:23.238
It's been in my family
ever since.

21:23.282 --> 21:25.806
Sounds like a story
that needs telling.

21:26.676 --> 21:27.851
Cheers to that.

21:27.895 --> 21:30.637
No, please. I'm fine, thank you.

21:30.680 --> 21:32.334
Anybody else? Please.

21:32.378 --> 21:34.989
[all chuckling]

21:35.032 --> 21:37.818
The size of the house
is misleading from outside.

21:37.861 --> 21:39.689
It's a very old building.

21:39.733 --> 21:41.038
The lighting and the shadows

21:41.082 --> 21:44.607
can play tricks with your mind,Cosmo.

21:44.651 --> 21:47.349
Well, let us know.

21:47.393 --> 21:51.266
- Wh... Are there any ghosts?
- [laughing]

21:51.310 --> 21:53.181
- Right, come on.
- Stop.

21:53.224 --> 21:54.443
With everybodythat died in the fire

21:54.487 --> 21:55.836
and living next toa funeral parlor,

21:55.879 --> 21:58.360
- I mean, come on.
- Not that I'm aware of.

21:58.404 --> 21:59.579
[Christina] You're ridiculous.

21:59.622 --> 22:03.844
I... I seen't a ghost one time.

22:03.887 --> 22:07.674
My hometown
is Wallace, North Carolina.

22:07.717 --> 22:09.676
That's where my family house is.

22:09.719 --> 22:13.680
And, you know,
I seen't a ghost there.

22:14.724 --> 22:16.422
I had to get out...

22:17.510 --> 22:19.207
It's such a small town,

22:19.250 --> 22:22.297
everybody seemed to be
backwards and stuck.

22:22.341 --> 22:26.432
Everything just
seemed stuck, yeah.

22:27.302 --> 22:29.043
I had to go.

22:29.086 --> 22:31.219
Wallace, you say.

22:32.176 --> 22:33.743
It's near Burgaw.

22:33.787 --> 22:36.050
Yes-yes, sir, it is.

22:37.704 --> 22:40.271
I spent some time in Burgaw.

22:40.837 --> 22:42.230
[Ottis] Really?

22:46.800 --> 22:51.326
Well, thank you for allowing meto be a part of your show.

22:52.849 --> 22:56.244
I'm opening my doors
to you all to film here,

22:56.287 --> 22:58.551
contributing to your cause,

22:58.594 --> 23:02.642
by letting you stay here
and by feeding you.

23:02.685 --> 23:06.428
In return, I have a few things.

23:06.472 --> 23:08.561
The interviewing
will be done at night.

23:08.604 --> 23:10.911
My schedule during the day
is full,

23:10.954 --> 23:14.001
and I do not wish
to complicate things.

23:19.136 --> 23:21.530
[Vincent VO]
Why so deep in thought child?

23:21.574 --> 23:24.925
Do you miss your parents,
Nancy?

23:27.493 --> 23:31.018
[normal voice] My mortician,
Randolph, is equally as busy,

23:31.061 --> 23:32.672
and I do not want to bother him.

23:32.715 --> 23:39.679
