Okay, if he had
something to do with it,

1:04:39.614 --> 1:04:41.660
then we'd be able to
find something down here then.

1:04:41.703 --> 1:04:44.663
He doesn't cast
a reflection in a mirror.

1:04:44.706 --> 1:04:47.448
Can we just...

1:04:47.492 --> 1:04:50.408
Can we just say
what needs to be said here?

1:04:50.451 --> 1:04:51.844
He's a fucking vampire.

1:04:51.888 --> 1:04:54.978
[laughing] A vampire?

1:04:55.021 --> 1:04:57.328
- Lex--
- That sounds
totally ridiculous.

1:04:57.371 --> 1:05:00.505
Did you just... Did you hearwhat just came outta your mouth?

1:05:00.548 --> 1:05:04.204
Okay, Seth, a vampire?

1:05:04.248 --> 1:05:06.206
- Hey, there's a jukebox.
- Lex.

1:05:06.250 --> 1:05:08.861
Al Jolson.

1:05:08.905 --> 1:05:10.036
Uh...

1:05:10.080 --> 1:05:12.517
"Happy Days Are Here To Stay."

1:05:12.560 --> 1:05:15.694
Damn, these records are old.

1:05:17.783 --> 1:05:19.872
Whoa, did you feel that?

1:05:19.916 --> 1:05:21.091
It's like déjà vu.

1:05:21.134 --> 1:05:22.831
Déjà vu.

1:05:24.355 --> 1:05:25.530
What?

1:05:25.573 --> 1:05:27.184
Déjà vu.

1:05:28.054 --> 1:05:29.534
It's him.

1:05:30.927 --> 1:05:33.451
He has been fucking with us.

1:05:37.890 --> 1:05:39.457
I know who...

1:05:40.545 --> 1:05:42.199
or what you are.

1:05:48.422 --> 1:05:50.511
You got me, Cosmo.

1:05:50.555 --> 1:05:54.951
You're right, I am a vampire.

1:05:54.994 --> 1:05:57.997
[laughing]

1:05:58.041 --> 1:05:59.259
See, Lex.

1:06:00.304 --> 1:06:02.132
I told you.

1:06:02.175 --> 1:06:04.003
Seth.

1:06:04.047 --> 1:06:05.613
What are you doing?

1:06:05.657 --> 1:06:08.660
I've been chasing missing peoplefor a long time.

1:06:09.791 --> 1:06:11.837
After a while,you develop a knack

1:06:11.880 --> 1:06:15.493
for identifying those
who stick out.

1:06:15.536 --> 1:06:19.236
Let me guess,
your Civil War story,

1:06:19.279 --> 1:06:21.978
- that's not your grandfather.
- Mm...

1:06:22.021 --> 1:06:23.414
It's you.

1:06:23.457 --> 1:06:24.937
The skin condition, the air.

1:06:24.981 --> 1:06:27.070
Very bright, Cosmo.

1:06:27.113 --> 1:06:29.028
Once again, you are correct.

1:06:29.072 --> 1:06:33.293
I am Dr. Vincent J. Miller.

1:06:33.337 --> 1:06:35.556
Those whack-a-do's upstairs,

1:06:35.600 --> 1:06:37.167
fussing around
with their equipment,

1:06:37.210 --> 1:06:39.430
trying to figure out
why they can't figure you out.

1:06:39.473 --> 1:06:43.390
- But we know why, don't we?
- Oh, we sure do, Cosmo.

1:06:43.434 --> 1:06:45.610
Who are you talking to?

1:06:45.653 --> 1:06:47.046
Cosmo.

1:06:48.265 --> 1:06:50.615
Seth, what are you doing?

1:06:53.487 --> 1:06:55.185
Let's have a drink, shall we?

1:06:57.578 --> 1:07:01.365
This is a very fine Kentucky
straight bourbon whiskey.

1:07:02.757 --> 1:07:05.021
It's rather old though.
I personally snatched it

1:07:05.064 --> 1:07:07.458
from General Grant's
headquarters.

1:07:11.940 --> 1:07:13.594
Very smooth.

1:07:28.783 --> 1:07:30.002
Don't spill it.

1:07:37.140 --> 1:07:40.534
Here's to 14 years
of being on the wagon.

1:07:40.578 --> 1:07:45.191
No, here's to being liberated
after 14 years.

1:07:45.235 --> 1:07:48.499
I was liberated at the end
of the Civil War

1:07:48.542 --> 1:07:50.544
by the woman who would
alter my life forever.

1:07:50.588 --> 1:07:52.677
[Lexy] Hello!
[clapping and snapping]

1:07:52.720 --> 1:07:54.679
Wake up, what are you doing?

1:07:56.985 --> 1:07:58.639
Have you been drinking?

1:08:02.904 --> 1:08:04.210
Ahh...

1:08:04.254 --> 1:08:08.084
[breathes deeply]

1:08:08.127 --> 1:08:10.129
Cosmo, what are you doing?

1:08:12.479 --> 1:08:14.916
He's pouring.

1:08:14.960 --> 1:08:17.354
- He's okay.
- Who are you talking to?

1:08:17.397 --> 1:08:18.703
Miller.

1:08:26.580 --> 1:08:29.061
Is that when you
turned into a vampire?

1:08:29.105 --> 1:08:31.411
- Yes.
- Seth, what are you doing?

1:08:31.455 --> 1:08:34.936
You do realize that you've put
everyone in grave danger

1:08:34.980 --> 1:08:38.026
with your unauthorized
investigation?

1:08:38.070 --> 1:08:40.638
Even your friends,
Richard and Carol,

1:08:40.681 --> 1:08:42.553
who are currently on their way.

1:08:42.596 --> 1:08:43.684
We gotta get outta here.

1:08:43.728 --> 1:08:45.773
Seth, come on, we gotta go!

1:08:45.817 --> 1:08:47.862
You're just trying to get
inside my head.

1:08:49.212 --> 1:08:51.083
You afraid of crucifixes
or some shit?

1:08:51.127 --> 1:08:55.870
[laughs]
I was raised Catholic.

1:08:55.914 --> 1:08:59.091
Crucifixes, holy water,
they don't work.

1:08:59.135 --> 1:09:01.311
[Lexy] Seth, let's go!

1:09:02.094 --> 1:09:03.791
Garlic, I love garlic.

1:09:03.835 --> 1:09:06.185
Growing in my backyard
as we speak.

1:09:06.229 --> 1:09:08.753
Seth! Seth...

1:09:08.796 --> 1:09:14.585
Stake through the heart,hurts like hell, won't kill me.

1:09:14.628 --> 1:09:17.065
Now, silver, mm.

1:09:17.109 --> 1:09:18.197
[Lexy] Come on, we gotta go.

1:09:18.241 --> 1:09:20.286
- That stings.
- [Lexy] Seth!

1:09:20.330 --> 1:09:21.809
Let's go!

1:09:21.853 --> 1:09:23.855
Seth! Seth!

1:09:23.898 --> 1:09:25.726
[grunting]

1:09:25.770 --> 1:09:26.814
No!

1:09:27.424 --> 1:09:28.642
No...

1:09:31.776 --> 1:09:33.125
[gasps]

1:09:34.648 --> 1:09:36.041
Please!

1:09:36.084 --> 1:09:39.262
[panting]

1:09:54.320 --> 1:09:55.539
Please!

1:10:01.371 --> 1:10:04.112
[screaming]

1:10:29.573 --> 1:10:31.531
